The paper focuses on the human factors in software development and the role of creativity in improving software products. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions the importance of studying creativity from a multidisciplinary view, which suggests a possible connection to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper proposes a research design that includes rarely employed methods in software engineering, which could be related to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper mentions the use of creativity to improvise solutions, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
